1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 g6 3.Nc3 Bg7 4.e4 {White naturally takes over the centre.} 
4...d6 {Preventing e5.} 5.Nf3 O-O {Black finished the development of the 
kingside and is now ready to play in the centre.} 6.Be2 {This is White's 
