knight from f6 and going ...Bf6-g5 (with or without ...f5).} 11.a3 {With 
this move White starts his queenside play immediately.} 11...h5 $1 {Since 
White wants to start immediate play on the queenside with Rb1 and b4 
Black's plan with ...f5 is rather slow. To illustrate, 
after 11.v..Ne8?!v12.Rb1f5 13.b4 White is ready to crash through with c5 even 
at the expense of a pawn, while Black's kingside play has little to show 
for. That is why he switches to the strategic idea of the exchange of the 
dark-squared bishops and plans to exchange them in one of the two ways: 
with ...Kh7 and ...Bh6, or ...Nh7 followed by ...Bf6-g5.} *

